so if god damns people to hell how is he good suppose you had a very serious illness and you went to the doctor and asked him to treat it then suppose he gave you a prescription that would cure your illness but you refused to take it who would be to blame if you failed to get better the doctor or you i think you know the answer in the same way the whole human race has a very serious spiritual illness it is a disease of our souls that the bible calls sin it is so serious in fact that it has put us on the road to eternal separation from god which is what the bible calls hell but listen god loves us and because he loves us he has provided the remedy for our spiritual disease the remedy is jesus christ who took the punishment we deserve when he died on the cross for us this is why the bible says for the wages of sin is death but the gift of god is eternal life in christ jesus our lord romans yes salvation is a free gift but what if we refuse it what if we fail to accept the remedy god has provided who then is to blame if we continue on the road away from god the answer is clear we are in other words god doesn't send us to hell we send ourselves don't gamble with your soul but by faith accept christ so you can know beyond doubt that you will go to be with him in heaven forever Justification (theology) Eastern Orthodox Church Sin Merit Sola fide Divine grace Hell Heaven Original sin Soul Resurrection of Jesus Baptism Comparing and contrasting Judaism and Christianity Immortality Christian eschatology Abrahamic religion Church of Jesus Christ of Latter-day Saints Predestination Roman Catholic Church A Course In Miracles Doctrines of Jehovah's Witnesses God Holy Spirit Indulgence Christianity Purgatory Trinity Religion Epistle to the Romans Church of Christ, Scientist Christian views of Jesus Problem of Hell Church of Christ Catholicism Book of Mormon Gospel of Thomas Jesus Eutheism, dystheism, and maltheism Afterlife The Pilgrim's Progress Religious pluralism Mormonism Infant baptism Harrowing of Hell Martin Luther Historical roots of Catholic Eucharistic theology John Howard Yoder Judas Iscariot Satan Philipp Melanchthon Reincarnation Sant Thakar Singh Creationism Catechism The Amber Spyglass Spiritism Mass (liturgy) Alan Campbell (pastor) Virgin Birth (Christian doctrine) Gospel of Barnabas Urantia Limbo Articles of Religion (Methodist) John the Baptist Salvation Army Jehovah's Witnesses Mary, the mother of Jesus Angel Sabbath Baptist Apostles' Creed Paul of Tarsus Religious perspectives on Jesus Mortification of the flesh Perseverance of the saints Christadelphians Book of Isaiah Jewish principles of faith Practices of Jehovah's Witnesses Meaning of life Charles Grandison Finney Devil John Wycliffe Legalism (theology) Moral objectivism Christian apologetics Calvinism Biblical inerrancy Aramaic of Jesus Prayer in Christianity Ascetical theology Five points of Calvinism Saint 